1
00:00:05,756 --> 00:00:11,887
♪

2
00:00:13,388 --> 00:01:42,144
♪

3
00:01:45,814 --> 00:01:48,358
(shouting)

4
00:01:48,358 --> 00:01:51,820
♪

5
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:52,863
This is it.

6
00:01:52,863 --> 00:01:55,782
Whoever can get ahead
for even one step,

7
00:01:55,782 --> 00:01:58,744
for even one second
is the winner.

8
00:01:58,744 --> 00:02:01,830
Simple, just how I like it.

9
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:03,874
(shouting)

10
00:02:05,417 --> 00:02:08,003
(shouting)

11
00:02:08,003 --> 00:02:09,129
(chuckles)

12
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:10,630
I'm gonna blind
you with the power

13
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:12,799
of my awesomeness, bug eyes!

14
00:02:12,799 --> 00:02:14,092
Bullshit.

15
00:02:14,092 --> 00:02:17,721
I call upon the wind,
the power of a raging storm!

16
00:02:17,721 --> 00:02:22,434
Super ultimate invincible!

17
00:02:24,102 --> 00:02:25,979
Oh, no!

18
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:27,939
No, not even close!

19
00:02:27,939 --> 00:02:29,191
And it looks
like his momentum

20
00:02:29,191 --> 00:02:33,403
has made him spin
out of c‐‐c‐‐control!

21
00:02:33,403 --> 00:02:35,447
No, he's accelerating.

22
00:02:35,447 --> 00:02:37,282
This was all
part of his plan.

23
00:02:37,282 --> 00:02:40,994
He's using centrifugal force
to power his fight!

24
00:02:40,994 --> 00:02:43,121
This is where the
real technique starts.

25
00:02:43,121 --> 00:02:46,291
God of the Wind, AT typhoon!

26
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:48,293
Bring it on, bitch.

27
00:02:48,293 --> 00:02:50,420
(shouting)

28
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:54,424
♪

29
00:02:54,424 --> 00:02:56,134
Do you think you
can blow me away

30
00:02:56,134 --> 00:02:57,969
with a little
breeze like that?

31
00:02:57,969 --> 00:03:00,138
I'll tear you to pieces!

32
00:03:00,138 --> 00:03:01,723
How you like me now?

33
00:03:01,723 --> 00:03:03,975
(grunting)

34
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:05,977
That stupid‐looking
technique worked!

35
00:03:05,977 --> 00:03:09,314
Their punches are
really kicking up dust.

36
00:03:09,314 --> 00:03:11,983
Woo, and here comes the Shark!

37
00:03:11,983 --> 00:03:13,402
You better watch it, Akira!

38
00:03:13,402 --> 00:03:15,904
You're leaving
yourself wide open!

39
00:03:15,904 --> 00:03:17,030
Ah!

40
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:18,240
Come on, you can do it.

41
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,658
This is my game now.

42
00:03:19,658 --> 00:03:21,660
You're finished!

43
00:03:21,660 --> 00:03:24,746
(grunting)

44
00:03:24,746 --> 00:03:26,706
(shouting)

45
00:03:28,041 --> 00:03:30,127
(roaring)

46
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:34,756
Fuck, two waves
at the same time?

47
00:03:34,756 --> 00:03:36,299
You did it, Akira.

48
00:03:36,299 --> 00:03:37,634
It's just like you said.

49
00:03:37,634 --> 00:03:40,053
Your fangs have evolved.

50
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:43,515
♪

51
00:03:43,515 --> 00:03:45,308
Akito, please.

52
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:46,560
I need your help.

53
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:48,854
Just one step, please.

54
00:03:48,854 --> 00:03:50,856
Just take one step
out of the cage.

55
00:03:50,856 --> 00:03:54,943
If we do it together,
we can make it.

56
00:03:54,943 --> 00:03:57,487
For just one blow,

57
00:03:57,487 --> 00:04:00,490
lend me your strength!

58
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:05,579
He's using the Leviathan's
Fang with our Regalia.

59
00:04:05,579 --> 00:04:07,831
How the hell is
that possible?

60
00:04:09,499 --> 00:04:12,085
(grunting)

61
00:04:13,545 --> 00:04:14,713
Hey, who's winning?

62
00:04:14,713 --> 00:04:15,714
I can't see anything!

63
00:04:15,714 --> 00:04:16,882
Just use the read!

64
00:04:16,882 --> 00:04:18,425
Check their power levels!

65
00:04:18,425 --> 00:04:20,594
Oh, right.

66
00:04:20,594 --> 00:04:21,636
(beep)

67
00:04:21,636 --> 00:04:24,014
It all comes down to the
strength of their fang.

68
00:04:24,014 --> 00:04:26,725
Whoever loses
gets blown away.

69
00:04:26,725 --> 00:04:28,560
(beeping)

70
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:30,437
Oh, no.

71
00:04:30,437 --> 00:04:32,189
I've had to use every
trick in the book

72
00:04:32,189 --> 00:04:34,858
to make it this far,
and for a second there,

73
00:04:34,858 --> 00:04:37,027
I actually thought
I could beat you.

74
00:04:37,027 --> 00:04:39,571
I hate to admit it,
but you win.

75
00:04:39,571 --> 00:04:42,365
Agito, I know you're
always bossing people around,

76
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:44,910
and you're still an annoying,
antisocial son of a bitch,

77
00:04:44,910 --> 00:04:47,037
but the truth is,
well, I mean,

78
00:04:47,037 --> 00:04:50,248
you really are a pain
in the ass, but, I mean‐‐

79
00:04:50,248 --> 00:04:51,500
Run for your life!

80
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,959
God, shut the hell up.

81
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:55,253
Why are you such a
whiny little bitch?

82
00:04:55,253 --> 00:04:58,423
But, damn, it's like my
feet are glued in place.

83
00:04:58,423 --> 00:05:00,133
I can't move an inch.

84
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:03,804
♪

85
00:05:03,804 --> 00:05:05,889
I'm sorry, Akito.

86
00:05:05,889 --> 00:05:08,642
It looks like I'm
useless after all.

87
00:05:10,227 --> 00:05:14,105
It's been fun, but I
guess this is goodbye.

88
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:16,149
(whooshing)

89
00:05:17,901 --> 00:05:20,070
We're not finished yet, Agito.

90
00:05:20,070 --> 00:05:21,363
Can you feel it?

91
00:05:21,363 --> 00:05:23,532
The wind's still blowing.

92
00:05:23,532 --> 00:05:26,034
(whooshing)

93
00:05:26,034 --> 00:05:28,119
(shouting)

94
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:29,079
Crow?

95
00:05:29,079 --> 00:05:31,498
Wait, what
happened to Mitsuru?

96
00:05:31,498 --> 00:05:33,458
♪

97
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:36,253
Ha, I'll be damned.

98
00:05:36,253 --> 00:05:37,587
Even in a place
like this dump,

99
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:40,048
I can still find a
nice tailwind to ride.

100
00:05:40,048 --> 00:05:42,968
He‐‐he's riding on my Fang.

101
00:05:42,968 --> 00:05:44,886
No way.

102
00:05:44,886 --> 00:05:46,054
He did it.

103
00:05:46,054 --> 00:05:48,515
The little crow
found a way to fly.

104
00:05:48,515 --> 00:05:53,812
♪

105
00:05:53,812 --> 00:05:56,064
I can see it.

106
00:05:56,064 --> 00:05:59,317
The Wing Road!

107
00:05:59,317 --> 00:06:00,485
What the hell?

108
00:06:00,485 --> 00:06:02,779
You've been in this
cage for too long.

109
00:06:02,779 --> 00:06:06,950
You don't even realize that
your wings are rotting off.

110
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:09,369
I'm gonna pick up
this whole damn cage

111
00:06:09,369 --> 00:06:11,830
and break through
and grab the sky!

112
00:06:11,830 --> 00:06:14,791
(whooshing)

113
00:06:17,794 --> 00:06:20,255
(swooshing)

114
00:06:23,842 --> 00:06:26,344
I may have been
afraid to admit it,

115
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:30,807
but I think deep down
I've always known.

116
00:06:32,893 --> 00:06:35,604
No matter how hard it may be,

117
00:06:35,604 --> 00:06:37,522
there's no such
thing as a bird

118
00:06:37,522 --> 00:06:40,901
that would rather stay
on the ground than fly.

119
00:06:42,861 --> 00:06:44,988
(whooshing)

120
00:06:44,988 --> 00:06:50,201
♪

121
00:06:50,201 --> 00:06:52,454
(shouting)

122
00:06:52,454 --> 00:07:08,553
♪

123
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:11,389
(clanging)

124
00:07:11,389 --> 00:07:13,933
They did it, those
Kogarasumaru bastards

125
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:15,518
actually pulled it off!

126
00:07:15,518 --> 00:07:16,978
With a final mighty roar,

127
00:07:16,978 --> 00:07:20,231
the Beast King came
tumbling down the mountain!

128
00:07:20,231 --> 00:07:22,192
(cheering)

129
00:07:22,192 --> 00:07:23,276
They did it, Ringo!

130
00:07:23,276 --> 00:07:25,654
I can't believe it!

131
00:07:25,654 --> 00:07:27,238
(chuckles)

132
00:07:27,238 --> 00:07:29,783
(cheering)

133
00:07:29,783 --> 00:07:31,660
They really are
something else.

134
00:07:31,660 --> 00:07:33,078
I think that punching contest

135
00:07:33,078 --> 00:07:35,455
was probably the turning
point of the match.

136
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:38,166
Yeah, you're right.

137
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:40,335
Ikki let Mitsuru
punch him in the stomach

138
00:07:40,335 --> 00:07:42,462
on purpose, right?

139
00:07:42,462 --> 00:07:44,589
Ugh, that crazy kid.

140
00:07:44,589 --> 00:07:45,965
I didn't make him
wear that thing

141
00:07:45,965 --> 00:07:47,676
so he could use it
to block punches.

142
00:07:47,676 --> 00:07:50,220
Ha‐ha, would you
rather he get hurt?

143
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:52,555
You know, I haven't
seen him in a while,

144
00:07:52,555 --> 00:07:54,182
but the Agito I know

145
00:07:54,182 --> 00:07:57,477
sure as hell never smiled
and laughed like that.

146
00:07:58,728 --> 00:08:00,814
(laughing)

147
00:08:00,814 --> 00:08:03,400
(gasping)

148
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:06,444
(roaring)

149
00:08:06,444 --> 00:08:07,529
(gasping)

150
00:08:07,529 --> 00:08:12,283
The battle may have ended,
but this isn't over.

151
00:08:12,283 --> 00:08:14,619
Akira!

152
00:08:16,329 --> 00:08:19,290
(grunting)

153
00:08:19,290 --> 00:08:22,293
(gasping)

154
00:08:22,293 --> 00:08:24,546
I still have my
mission as a king.

155
00:08:24,546 --> 00:08:27,090
Don't forget that.

156
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:28,800
You punk!

157
00:08:30,677 --> 00:08:32,637
(shouting)

158
00:08:34,305 --> 00:08:37,142
(gasping)

159
00:08:37,142 --> 00:08:41,229
Listen, Crow, or maybe
I should say Ikki,

160
00:08:41,229 --> 00:08:43,189
it was a good battle.

161
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:46,568
I'm impressed.

162
00:08:46,568 --> 00:08:49,195
♪

163
00:08:49,195 --> 00:08:50,780
But don't get cocky.

164
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:53,658
You aren't ready
to be king yet.

165
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:58,163
Ha, look who's talking,
you pointy‐haired asshole.

166
00:08:58,163 --> 00:09:01,875
But still I have to admit
you're pretty strong.

167
00:09:01,875 --> 00:09:04,377
And this is gonna hurt.

168
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:07,047
(slamming)

169
00:09:07,047 --> 00:09:09,382
(gasping)

170
00:09:10,925 --> 00:09:13,678
(grunting)

171
00:09:13,678 --> 00:09:17,057
Where'd he go?

172
00:09:17,057 --> 00:09:19,517
(gasping)

173
00:09:20,852 --> 00:09:23,146
Akira.

174
00:09:23,146 --> 00:09:31,863
♪

175
00:09:31,863 --> 00:09:33,698
It's okay.

176
00:09:33,698 --> 00:09:35,158
It's over.

177
00:09:35,158 --> 00:09:37,368
You kept your promise.

178
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:42,207
You can finally rest now.

179
00:09:42,207 --> 00:09:45,335
♪

180
00:09:45,335 --> 00:09:47,629
Dude, that's crazy.

181
00:09:47,629 --> 00:09:50,381
I think he just
passed out standing up.

182
00:09:50,381 --> 00:09:52,425
(crying)

183
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:55,970
It is over!

184
00:09:55,970 --> 00:09:59,099
(shouting)

185
00:10:04,104 --> 00:10:07,690
♪

186
00:10:07,690 --> 00:10:11,402
This is just what I'd expect
from an old sewage plant.

187
00:10:11,402 --> 00:10:14,405
Filthy, smelly,
and packed full of shit.

188
00:10:14,405 --> 00:10:16,324
But that's all right
'cause it's about to get

189
00:10:16,324 --> 00:10:18,827
one hell of a cleaning.

190
00:10:18,827 --> 00:10:24,290
♪

191
00:10:28,253 --> 00:10:33,049
♪

192
00:10:33,049 --> 00:10:35,260
Come on.

193
00:10:35,260 --> 00:10:38,429
All right, and, now,
for the grand finale...

194
00:10:38,429 --> 00:10:39,889
...Kogarasumaru!

195
00:10:39,889 --> 00:10:42,851
Please, I'm way too
tired to do this.

196
00:10:44,519 --> 00:10:46,855
Victory pose!

197
00:10:46,855 --> 00:10:48,857
(whooshing)

198
00:10:50,275 --> 00:10:53,319
Hey, I'm not trying to rain
on your parade or anything,

199
00:10:53,319 --> 00:10:55,446
but I think you're getting
a little ahead of yourselves.

200
00:10:55,446 --> 00:10:57,699
We haven't decided
a winner yet.

201
00:10:57,699 --> 00:10:59,993
Let's see, the last one
standing was Agito

202
00:10:59,993 --> 00:11:01,119
and the Crow knocked
out the Hammer,

203
00:11:01,119 --> 00:11:02,787
but then the King
knocked out the Crow.

204
00:11:02,787 --> 00:11:04,831
That means‐‐hell,
I don't know.

205
00:11:04,831 --> 00:11:06,499
This has never
happened before.

206
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:07,876
Even I'm confused.

207
00:11:07,876 --> 00:11:10,295
The match is the least
of our concerns.

208
00:11:10,295 --> 00:11:12,505
Someone could die if
this mob gets uglier.

209
00:11:12,505 --> 00:11:14,340
Uh, I'm getting scared.

210
00:11:14,340 --> 00:11:17,218
Yeah, the mood in here is
starting to get kind of sucky.

211
00:11:17,218 --> 00:11:19,179
Are we gonna be okay?

212
00:11:19,179 --> 00:11:21,723
I've never seen so many
rioters in one place before,

213
00:11:21,723 --> 00:11:24,517
and they're all
Behemoth fans too.

214
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:26,311
Maybe we should get going.

215
00:11:26,311 --> 00:11:29,063
The Fang of the great
beast has been broken.

216
00:11:29,063 --> 00:11:31,858
Huh?

217
00:11:31,858 --> 00:11:34,736
Everyone here has seen
it with their own eyes.

218
00:11:34,736 --> 00:11:37,488
There is no room for debate.

219
00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:40,658
Behemoth has lost.

220
00:11:40,658 --> 00:11:42,869
(booing)

221
00:11:42,869 --> 00:11:44,954
♪

222
00:11:44,954 --> 00:11:47,040
Yeah, they're getting
uglier, all right.

223
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:49,959
All right, everyone, let's
just proceed to the exit

224
00:11:49,959 --> 00:11:51,252
in an orderly fashion.

225
00:11:51,252 --> 00:11:52,670
Just don't hurt me.

226
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:55,173
(booing)

227
00:11:55,173 --> 00:11:57,342
♪

228
00:11:57,342 --> 00:11:58,509
What's going on?

229
00:11:58,509 --> 00:12:00,762
‐Huh?
‐What?

230
00:12:00,762 --> 00:12:02,013
Huh?

231
00:12:02,013 --> 00:12:04,307
♪

232
00:12:04,307 --> 00:12:07,685
It's the Shinjuku
Crocodile and his G‐Men.

233
00:12:07,685 --> 00:12:09,687
♪

234
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:11,856
(clicking)

235
00:12:11,856 --> 00:12:13,858
♪

236
00:12:13,858 --> 00:12:16,361
(coughing)

237
00:12:16,361 --> 00:12:19,405
♪

238
00:12:19,405 --> 00:12:22,033
(groaning and shouting)

239
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:24,994
Come on!

240
00:12:24,994 --> 00:12:26,746
Ah!

241
00:12:26,746 --> 00:12:28,915
Oh, my God!

242
00:12:28,915 --> 00:12:32,460
Bastards sure took
their time getting here.

243
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:33,586
Come on, let's go!

244
00:12:33,586 --> 00:12:34,587
We better get out of here

245
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:35,713
while we still
have the chance!

246
00:12:35,713 --> 00:12:38,383
Buccha, take the Crow with
you while you're at it.

247
00:12:38,383 --> 00:12:40,885
He's like a frigging
monkey on my back.

248
00:12:40,885 --> 00:12:43,930
Agito, you did this,
didn't you?

249
00:12:43,930 --> 00:12:45,431
You tipped them off
because you knew

250
00:12:45,431 --> 00:12:47,809
this would happen if we won.

251
00:12:47,809 --> 00:12:50,353
(grunting)

252
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:54,315
Two years, ha.

253
00:12:54,315 --> 00:12:57,068
I guess we've both changed,
haven't we, Akira?

254
00:12:57,068 --> 00:13:01,572
Yeah, look at us, surrounded
by all these noisy morons.

255
00:13:01,572 --> 00:13:04,242
With punk‐ass shits
like that hanging around,

256
00:13:04,242 --> 00:13:05,952
it's hard to get
any rest, you know?

257
00:13:05,952 --> 00:13:09,580
You can rest all you want
when you're back in your cage.

258
00:13:09,580 --> 00:13:12,166
Don't worry, all your
noisy punk‐ass friends

259
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:13,334
are getting locked up, too.

260
00:13:13,334 --> 00:13:15,503
Now let's go home,
you little piece of shit.

261
00:13:15,503 --> 00:13:17,839
‐Ah!
‐No!

262
00:13:19,257 --> 00:13:21,592
My shoulder can't hold out.

263
00:13:21,592 --> 00:13:23,761
Akira!

264
00:13:23,761 --> 00:13:25,763
You haven't even
been gone a month,

265
00:13:25,763 --> 00:13:27,140
but I've been so lonely.

266
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:29,183
It felt like a
thousand years.

267
00:13:29,183 --> 00:13:32,645
Why do you have to make
your brother sad, Agito?

268
00:13:32,645 --> 00:13:35,440
Well, what do you have to say?

269
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:37,567
You're a son of a bitch.

270
00:13:37,567 --> 00:13:40,611
You want me to wash your
mouth out with soap, huh?

271
00:13:40,611 --> 00:13:42,989
That's not fucking soap.

272
00:13:42,989 --> 00:13:44,782
Taking it a little far,
don't you think?

273
00:13:44,782 --> 00:13:47,118
It looks bad, but that's
